term_definition: Proportion of salmon mortality attributed to mainstem phase.
notes: column_name=mainstem_mortality_rate; No canonical mortality-rate subclass exists yet.

term_definition: Proportion of salmon mortality attributed to ocean phase.
notes: column_name=ocean_mortality_rate; No canonical mortality-rate subclass exists yet.

term_definition: Proportion of salmon mortality attributed to terminal phase.
notes: column_name=terminal_mortality_rate; No canonical mortality-rate subclass exists yet.

term_definition: Marine survival rate estimated from coded-wire-tag data.
notes: column_name=cwt_marine_survival_rate; No canonical marine-survival class exists yet.

term_definition: Proportion of salmon mortality occurring during in-river migration.
notes: column_name=in_river_mortality_rate; No canonical mortality-rate subclass exists yet.

term_definition: Total mortality proportion across all phases for a reporting unit and year.
notes: column_name=total_mortality_rate; No canonical total mortality-rate subclass exists yet.

term_definition: Proportion of spawning fish of hatchery origin in a reporting unit and year.
notes: column_name=phos; Widely used indicator; no canonical pHOS class yet.

term_definition: Indexed marine survival metric used in indicator/population summaries.
notes: column_name=marine_survival_index; No canonical marine-survival-index class exists yet.

term_definition: Scalar factor used to expand observed counts to estimated totals.
notes: column_name=expansion_factor; May also be modeled as method/procedure metadata.

term_definition: Abundance of spawners in a unit and year.

term_definition: Relative spawner abundance metric normalized to a baseline.

term_definition: Relative abundance of hatchery-origin spawners normalized to a baseline.
